<blockquote>
<p>
If someone tries to end a debate about programming languages by
invoking Turing Equivalence, you are allowed to give them a long reel
of tape and steal their laptop.
</p>
</blockquote>

<p>
If mathematical equivalence were the only thing that mattered in
language design, we'd all be using Turing tape. Turing Equivalence is
what qualifies a language to enter the debate, not what finishes it.
</p><img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/KrisJenkinsBlog/~4/FgNGIiFI3pM" height="1" width="1"/>